TASK_DESCRIPTION=Running 'doey yo' prints 'Unknown command: yo' and exits without invoking the intent fallback (Haiku-powered correction via shell/intent-fallback.sh + shell/doey-intent-dispatch.sh). Unknown commands are supposed to route through the fallback so Claude can interpret intent. Investigate why the unknown-command path is not calling the fallback — possible broken wiring in shell/doey.sh dispatch, or DOEY_NO_INTENT_FALLBACK set, or fallback script erroring silently. See docs/intent-fallback.md.
